FBIS4-13076 "drnes074_p_94004" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan UN Mission Meets With Dostum, Leaves for Herat UN Mission Meets With Dostum, Leaves for Herat LD1804084994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0730 GMT 18 Apr 94 LD1804084994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Continuing their meetings with the leaders of the rival Afghan groups, the UN delegation left Mazar-e Sharif for Herat yesterday. The members of this delegation are to hold talks with the provincial governor of Herat, who is a member of Jamiat-e Eslami. Before leaving Mazar-e Sharif, Mahmud Mestiri, the leader of the UN delegation, had another meeting with Abdol Rashid Dostum, the leader of the National-Islamic Movement of Afghanistan. According to the Central News Unit from Islamabad, Dostum said the only way to establish peace in Afghanistan is for Rabbani to resign as president.
